## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-102">これは、`enum`のイベントが発生したときに、イベントの種類を指定、<xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject>です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-102">This `enum` specifies the event type when an event is raised for an <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-103">XML ツリーを変更するすべての操作は、一連のプリミティブに分割します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-103">All operations that modify the XML tree break down to a series of primitives.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-104">プリミティブの 4 つの種類があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-104">There are four types of primitives.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-105">2 つのプリミティブ (追加および削除) は、コレクションに対して作用します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-105">Two of the primitives (Add and Remove) act on collections.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-106">(名前と値) の 2 つは、インスタンスに対して作用します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-106">Two of them (Name and Value) act on instances.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-107">これらのプリミティブの列ごとの対応するイベントがあります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-107">There is a corresponding event for each of these primitives.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-108">これを行うために、これらのイベントのいずれかの中の XML ツリーを変更するとき、注意する必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-108">You should be careful when modifying an XML tree within one of these events, because doing this might lead to unexpected results.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-109">たとえば、受信する場合、<xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changing>イベントとイベントの処理中には、ツリーからノードを削除する、できない場合があります、<xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changed>イベント。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-109">For example, if you receive a <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changing> event, and while the event is being processed you remove the node from the tree, you might not receive the <xref:System.Xml.Linq.XObject.Changed> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-110">イベントの処理中は、それが有効では以外のイベントを受信しているノードが含まれる XML ツリーを変更するには指定の変更イベントが発生した特定のノードには影響しません、同じツリーを変更するでも有効です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-110">When an event is being processed, it is valid to modify an XML tree other than the one that contains the node that is receiving the event; it is even valid to modify the same tree provided the modifications do not affect the specific nodes on which the event was raised.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1862-111">ただし、イベントを受け取るノードを含むツリーの領域を変更する場合に表示されるイベントと、ツリーへの影響は未定義です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-111">However, if you modify the area of the tree that contains the node receiving the event, the events that you receive and the impact to the tree are undefined.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-112">次の例では、ツリーに要素を追加することでイベントを発生させます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-112">The following example raises an event by adding an element to the tree.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root", "content");  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Add(new XElement("Child", "child content"));  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-113">この例を実行すると、次の出力が生成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-113">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Add  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Add  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-114">次の例では、ツリーから要素を削除することでイベントを発生させます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-114">The following example raises an event by removing an element from the tree.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root",  
    new XElement("Child", "content")  
);  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Element("Child").Remove();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-115">この例を実行すると、次の出力が生成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-115">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Remove  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Remove  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-116">次の例では、要素の名前を変更することによって、イベントを発生させます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-116">The following example raises an event by changing the name of an element.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root", "content");  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Name = "NewName";  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-117">この例を実行すると、次の出力が生成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-117">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changing: Name  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XElement  
  Changed: Name  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-118">次の例では、属性の値を設定してイベントを発生させます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-118">The following example raises an event by setting the value of an attribute.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
XElement root = new XElement("Root",  
    new XAttribute("Att", "att value")  
);  
root.Changing += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changing event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changing: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.Changed += (sender, e) =>  
    {  
        Console.WriteLine("Changed event raised");  
        Console.WriteLine("  Sender: " + sender.GetType());  
        Console.WriteLine("  Changed: " + e.ObjectChange);  
    };  
root.FirstAttribute.Value = "new contents";  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1862-119">この例を実行すると、次の出力が生成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1862-119">This example produces the following output:</span></span>  
  
```  
Changing event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XAttribute  
  Changing: Value  
Changed event raised  
  Sender: System.Xml.Linq.XAttribute  
  Changed: Value  
```
